President Obama met with independent financial regulators to discuss the ongoing implementation of Wall Street Reform. He commended the regulators for their efforts to strengthen the financial system through the Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act. The President emphasized the importance of maintaining capital standards and prudent capital cushions, particularly for the largest global firms. He also urged regulators to consider ways to prevent excessive risk-taking and to evaluate the effectiveness of their actions. The participants discussed the need for continued coordination through the Financial Stability Oversight Council and the need for additional resources and stable funding for market regulators. The meeting included regulators such as Janet Yellen, Mary Jo White, and Martin Gruenberg, as well as White House and administration participants.